@node "Connector.Init"
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Init

   SYNOPSIS
       Init

   FUNCTION
       Same as the Init button the Connector GUI.  If no user us online,
       the initialisation code set in the Serial preferences for the
       current line is sent to the modem.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful.
       10 -- User online.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.Hangup" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Hangup

   SYNOPSIS
       Hangup

   FUNCTION
       Hangs up the modem; has the effect of booting the current user
       offline.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
       10 -- No caller online.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.Quit" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Quit

   SYNOPSIS
       Quit

   FUNCTION
       Quits the connector.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.Query" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Query

   SYNOPSIS
       Query <ON|OFF>

   FUNCTION
       Switches the query display on the Connector GUI on or off.

   INPUTS
       ON  -- enables query display
       OFF -- disables query display

   RESULT

   RC

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.Smodem" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SModem

   SYNOPSIS
       SModem <Command>

   FUNCTION
       Sends the @{i}modem@{ui} command given to the modem if there is
       no user online.

   INPUTS
       Command -- Modem command to send.

   RESULT

   RC

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.Online" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Online

   SYNOPSIS
       Online

   FUNCTION
       Returns the state of the line, to indicate if there is a caller
       or not.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- No caller.
       5 -- Caller online.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.OpenDev" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       OpenDev

   SYNOPSIS
       OpenDev

   FUNCTION
       Opens the serial device and returns its state.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Serial device is open, Connector is ready.
        5 -- Device was already open, Connector is ready.
       10 -- Device failed to open.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Connector.CloseDev" }  
@toc Connector
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       CloseDev

   SYNOPSIS
       CloseDev

   FUNCTION
       Closes the serial device.  Connector cannot answer calls if a serial
       device is not open.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successfully closed.
       5 -- Device was already closed.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ########                                                              ########
; ########                       FED AREXX Commands                     ########          
; ########                                                              ########
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################

@node "FEDDisplayUser"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDDisplayUser

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDDisplayUser <Text>

   FUNCTION
       Opens a window on screen with the given text, which the
       user must okay to continue.

   INPUTS
       Text  -- Text to display to user.

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful.
       5 -- Bad args.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDRequest"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDRequest

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDRequest <Text> [Buttons] [Title]

   FUNCTION
       Opens a window, as with FEDDisplayUser, but also allows
       the user to specify between given options.

   INPUTS
       Text    -- Text to display to the user.
       Buttons -- The buttons of the requester. Each button is
                  separated by a "|". Defaults to "Yes|No".
       Title   -- If buttons are given, then a title may be
                  specified also. Defaults to "Important
                  Request".

   RESULT

   RC
       10 -- Bad arguments.

       Otherwise, the number of the button the user specified,
       0 representing the far right option (most negative)
       then starting with 1 on the left. i.e.:

            "Yes|Maybe|No"

              1    2    0

   EXAMPLE

       /**/

       options results

       address ZEUS
       FEDRequest '"Hello from the test script"' '"Hi|Hello|Goodbye"' '"Hihi"'
       say RC

   NOTES
       Note that you cannot safely have 11 buttons as 10 is
       used as an error return code.

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDGetCurrentAreaNumber"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDGetCurrentAreaNumber

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDGetCurrentAreaNumber

   FUNCTION
       Returns the number of the area currently displayed.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       Area Number (0 if none displayed)

   RC
       0 -- Always successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDGetCurrentFileName"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDGetCurrentFileName

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDGetCurrentFileName

   FUNCTION
       Returns the name of the selected file.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       Selected file's name.

   RC
       0 -- Successful
       2 -- Could not find name
       5 -- No file selected or in DOS listing mode

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDGetCurrentFullPath"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDGetCurrentFullPath

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDGetCurrentFullPath

   FUNCTION
       Returns the name and path of the selected file.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       Selected file's full path

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        2 -- Could not find name
        5 -- No file selected or in DOS listing mode
       10 -- Could not find area

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDInDosMode"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDInDosMode

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDInDosMode

   FUNCTION
       Is the FileEditor in DOS mode?

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       -1 -- DOS mode
        0 -- Zeus files mode

   RC
       0 -- Always successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO


@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDGetPublicScreen"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDGetPublicScreen

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDGetPublicScreen

   FUNCTION
       Returns the name of the screen FileEditor is on.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       Selected screen's name.

   RC
       0 -- Always successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDReloadFile"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDReloadFile

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDReloadFile

   FUNCTION
       Reloads the details for the current file.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Always successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDReloadList"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDReloadList

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDReloadList

   FUNCTION
       Reloads the list of files for the current area.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Always successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "FEDThere"
@toc FED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       FEDThere

   SYNOPSIS
       FEDThere

   FUNCTION
       Tests if the FileEditor is loaded.  If it isn't, this
       command will fail.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful, therefore the FileEditor is in memory.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ########                                                              ########
; ########                      File AREXX Commands                     ########          
; ########                                                              ########
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################
; ##############################################################################

@node ADDFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       AddFile

   SYNOPSIS
       AddFile '"<FILENAME>"' [AREA] [DESCRIPTION '"<DESC>"']|[DESCFILE '<FILE>']
               [UNVALIDATED] [FREEFILE] [UPLOADER '"<NAME>"'] [OFFLINE]

   FUNCTION
       Adds a file to the file bases.

   INPUTS
       FILENAME    -- File (and path if necessary) to add.
       AREA        -- Area number to add to.
       DESCRIPTION -- String to use as the file's description.
       DESCFILE    -- Alternately, a file to load for the description.
       UNVALIDATED -- The file is added unvalidated.
       FREEFILE    -- Make this file a free download.
       UPLOADER    -- Name of the user who uploaded the file.  This does
                      not have to be the name of an existing user, for
                      example "ZeusRexx Uploader" is valid.
       OFFLINE     -- Mark the file as off-line.

   RESULT
       If RC = 1, then the reason for failure.  One of:

       No such file area!
       File does not exist!
       File already exists!
       Fatal Error!
       Bad File Name!
       Disk Error!

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        1 -- Upload failure
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node BEGINSCANAREAS
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       BeginScanAreas

   SYNOPSIS
       BeginScanAreas <CHRONO | NATURAL | ALPHA> <FORWARDS | BACKWARDS> [WRAP <NUM>]
                      [INDENT <NUM>] [INDENTLINE] [MAXLINES <NUM>] [AREA <NUM>]

   FUNCTION
       Initialises a file scan on the current line for the given
       area.  If AREA is not given then the current area is used.

       This must be finished with a call to EndScanAreas after
       use with NextScanFile.

   INPUTS
       CHRONO     -- Scan files in the order they were uploaded.
       NATURAL    -- Scan files in the order Zeus loads them.
       ALPHA      -- Scan files alphabetically.
       FORWARDS   -- Scan files from top to bottom.
       BACKWARDS  -- Scan files from bottom to top.

       WRAP       -- The number of characters to wrap the description at.
       INDENT     -- The number of spaces to indent the file description lines
                     that follow a word wrap on the user's screen.

       INDENTLINE -- Indent the first line of the description.
       MAXLINES   -- Maximum number of lines to display from the descriptions.
                     Defaults to all lines.
       AREA       -- The area number to scan.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Area initilized for use.
        2 -- User does not have access to area.
       10 -- Unable to scan area.
       15 -- Bad arguments.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"NextScanFile" link "NextScanFile"} @{"EndScanAreas" link "EndScanAreas"} @{"PrintFileDesc" link "PrintFileDesc"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node CHANGEFILEAREA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       ChangeFileArea

   SYNOPSIS
       ChangeFileArea <Number> [ALL]

   FUNCTION
       Change the current file area of the current line/user.

   INPUTS
       Number -- Area number to change to.
       ALL    -- Ignore SIG ranges.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Area changed.
        2 -- User does not have access to area.
        5 -- No such file area.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"ChangeSIG" link "ChangeSIG"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node CHANGEXPRPROTO
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       ChangeXPRProto

   SYNOPSIS
       ChangeXprProto <Number>

   FUNCTION
       Changes the XPR file transfer protocol used by the
       online user to the specified one.

   INPUTS
       Number -- XPR protocol's ordinal number in the Zeus
                 configuration (see @{"GetProtocolInto" link "GetProtocolInto"})

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Protocol Changed.
       2 -- User does not have access to protocol.
       5 -- No such protocol.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"GetProtocolInfo" link "GetProtocolInfo"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node CHECKNEWFILES
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       CheckNewFiles

   SYNOPSIS
       CheckNewFiles

   FUNCTION
       Checks for, but does not list, any new files in the
       current area based on the information set by @{"SetFileFilter" link "SetFileFilter"}.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- There are new files in the area.
        5 -- There are no new files.
       10 -- File filter not active.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"SetFileFilter" link "SetFileFilter"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node CLOSEFILEKEY
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       CloseFileKey

   SYNOPSIS
       CloseFileKey <KEY>

   FUNCTION
       Close and deallocate resources taken by a file key
       initialised with InitFileKey.

   INPUTS
       KEY -- Key are returned by InitFileKey

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO
       @{"InitFileKey" link "InitFileKey"} @{"GetFileFromKey" link "GetFileFromKey"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node CONVERTDATE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       ConvertDate

   SYNOPSIS
       ConvertDate '"<DATE>"'

   FUNCTION
       Converts a textual date into Zeus' internal format.

   INPUTS
       DATE -- Date string in the format "dd mmm yy hh:mm:ss", eg.
               "30 Jun 99 16:20:32".  Also acceptable are reduced
               forms to a minimum of "dd mmm yy" - the missing
               values will be taken as 0.

   RESULT
       Converted date in seconds since 1-Jan-70 00:00:00.

   RC
        0 -- Date converted and stored in RESULT
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO
       @{"Strftime" link "Strftime"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node COPYTEMPLATELIMITS
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       CopyTemplateLimits

   SYNOPSIS
       CopyTemplateLimits

   FUNCTION
       Set the users area access settings to the default
       template settings.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node DELAY
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Delay

   SYNOPSIS
       Delay <Ticks>

   FUNCTION
       Delay the further execution of the script for a set time.

   INPUTS
       Ticks -- Number of `ticks' to delay for.  Each tick is one
                50th of a second, so "Seconds*50" gives the correct
                value.

   RESULT

   RC

   EXAMPLE
       /* Delay for 10 seconds */

       Parse Arg Line

       Options Results

       Write '"Delaying for 10 seconds.."'

       Delay 50*10  /* 50 ticks (1 second) * 10 */

       Write '"Done!"'

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node DELETECATFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       DeleteCatFile

   SYNOPSIS
       DeleteCatFile FILENAME '"<FILE>"' NUMBER <NUM> [DELETE]

   FUNCTION
       Deletes a file from the Zeus file catalogue.  This can also
       delete the file itself.  This command is potentially
       dangerous if used by normal users.

   INPUTS
       FILE    -- Name of file to delete from the catalogues.
       NUM     -- Alternatively, the number of the file to delete
                  from the catalogues.
       DELETE  -- If set, the file will be deleted from disk also.

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- File deleted
       5 -- No such file

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node DELETEFILEFILTER
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       DeleteFileFilter

   SYNOPSIS
       DeleteFileFilter

   FUNCTION
       Remove the file filter for this line which was set with
       SetFileFilter.

   INPUTS

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"SetFileFilter" link "SetFileFilter"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node DOWNLOAD
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Download

   SYNOPSIS
       Download [FILE '"<FILE>"' | <NUM>] [DOSFILE '"<FILES"'] [FILEDESC]

   FUNCTION
       Begin a file download.  If no files are specified, then the user's
       marked files will be sent.

   INPUTS
       FILE    -- Name or number of a file in the Zeus file catalogues.
       DOSFILE -- List of files to download which are not in the Zeus
                  file catalogue.  Seperate each file with a space.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successfully started transfer of files
       10 -- Unable to start file transfer
       15 -- No files to transfer

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node EDITFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       EditFile

   SYNOPSIS
       EditFile FILENAME '"<FILE>" NUMBER <NUM> [SIZE <NUM>] [LASTDL '"<DATE>"']
                [UPLOADED '"<DATE>"'] [UPLOADEDBY '"<NAME>"'] [DOWNLOADS <NUM>]
                [VALIDATED] [UNVALIDATED] [FREE] [NOFREE] [OFFLINE] [ONLINE]
                [DESCFILE '"<FILENAME>"']

   FUNCTION
       Edit the attributes of a file.

   INPUTS
       FILENAME    -- The name of the file to edit.
       NUMBER      -- The number of the file to edit.
       SIZE        -- New size for the specified file.
       LASTDL      -- Last download date for the file.
       UPLOADED    -- The date the file was uploaded.
       UPLOADEDBY  -- Who uploaded the file.
       DOWNLOADS   -- Number of downloads the file has had.
       VALIDATED   -- Make file validated.
       UNVALIDATED -- Make file unvalidated.
       FREE        -- Make this file free.
       NOFREE      -- Make this file not free.
       OFFLINE     -- File is offline.
       ONLINE      -- File is online.
       DESCFILE    -- The file to use as the file's description.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- File edited.
        2 -- Unable to edit file.
        4 -- Description file invalid.
        5 -- No such file.
       10 -- Bad aguments.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node ENDLIST
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       EndList

