@node GETFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetFile

   SYNOPSIS
       GetFile < NAME '"<FILENAME>"' | NUMBER <NUM> > [ENTRY] [POINTER]
               [FILENUMBER] [FILENAME] [SIZE] [UPLOADED] [LASTDL] [DLS]
               [UPLOADER] [UNVALIDATED] [FREE] [OFFLINE] [WRAP <NUM>]
               [MAXLINES <NUM>] [DESC]

   FUNCTION
       Returns information on the specified file.

   INPUTS
       NAME        -- The name of the file to get information from.
       NUMBER      -- The number of the file to get information from.

       ENTRY       -- Ask for the file's entry.
       POINTER     -- Ask for the file's pointer.
       FILENUMBER  -- Get the file's number.
       FILENAME    -- Get the files.
       SIZE        -- Get the file's size.
       UPLOADED    -- Return the date the file was uploaded.
       LASTDL      -- The date the file was last downloaded.
       DLS         -- The number of times the file has been downloaded.
       UPLOADER    -- The name of the user who uploaded the file.
       UNVALIDATED -- Check if the file is unvalidated.
       FREE        -- Check if the file is free.
       OFFLINE     -- Check if the file is offline.
       WRAP        -- Wrap description after <NUM> chars.
       MAXLINES    -- Only return <NUM> lines of the description.
       DESC        -- Return the description.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Data retrieved and stored in RESULT.
        5 -- Unable to load file.
       10 -- Bad arguments.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETFILEACCESS
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetFileAccess

   SYNOPSIS
       GetFileAccess <ACCESS | VIEW | DOWNLOAD | UPLOAD | EDITOWN | EDITALL |
                     UNVALIDATED | VALIDATE | DELETE | SYSOP | MASKEDOUT> [AREA]

   FUNCTION
       Checks whether the user online can access various
       attributes of a given file area.

       If an area is not specified, the current area
       is checked.

   INPUTS
       ACCESS      -- Check if user has access to the area.
       VIEW        -- Check if user can view files.
       DOWNLOAD    -- Download access.
       UPLOAD      -- Upload Access.
       EDITOWN     -- Edit own file uploads.
       EDITALL     -- Edit all file uploads.
       UNVALIDATED -- This file area does not require file validation.
       VALIDATE    -- This area requires file validation.
       DELETE      -- User can delete files.
       SYSOP       -- User has SysOp Access in this area.
       MASKEDOUT   -- This file area is masked out by user.

       AREA        -- The number of the area to work with.

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Flag is NOT set.
       1 -- Flag is set.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETFILEAREA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetFileArea

   SYNOPSIS
       GetFileArea [ORDINAL] <AREA> [NAME] [ PATH [<NUM>] ] [NUMBER] [UNIQUE] [LOW]
                   [HIGH] [MINDLBAUD] [MINULBAUD] [MINAGE] [DOWNLOADS] [UPLOADS]
                   [VIEWING] [FREEFILES] [VALIDATION] [DOSNAMES] [COPYTOTEMP]
                   [FILELIB]

   FUNCTION
       Get information on a file area.  BOOLs are returns as
       1 for True, 0 for False, as per standard ARexx.

   INPUTS
       ORDINAL    -- See NOTE for information.
       AREA       -- The number of the area to get information from.

       NAME       -- The name of the file area.
       PATH       -- The main path of the file area if <NUM> is not
                     supplied, otherwise the MultiPath corrisponding
                     to <NUM>.
       NUMBER     -- The number of the file area
       UNIQUE     -- (obsolete) Unique file area number.
       LOW        -- Low access to area.
       HIGH       -- High access to area.
       MINDLBAUD  -- Minimum baud rate to download.
       MINULBAUD  -- Minimum baud rate to upload.
       MINAGE     -- Minimum age for access to area. (BOOL)
       DOWNLOADS  -- Allow downloads.  (BOOL)
       UPLOADS    -- Allow uploads. (BOOL)
       VIEWING    -- Allow archive/file viewing. (BOOL)
       FREEFILES  -- All files in area are free.  (BOOL)
       VALIDATION -- File validation required. (BOOL)
       DOSNAMES   -- Area uses IBM/PC style filenames (8.3). (BOOL)
       COPYTOTEMP -- Files are copied to temporary directory. (BOOL)
       FILELIB    -- Name of File Library in use. This returns the
                     library's 4 character ID code.

   RESULT
       Data requested.

   RC
        0 -- Information retrieved and stored in RESULT.
       10 -- Bad aruments.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

       ORDINAL -- This keyword MUST appear before the AREA argument for it to
             work. The ORDINAL option is similiar to a NEXT keyword, meaning
             that if the specified AREA does not exist then the next available
             area will used.

             eg. If you do not have an area #10, but have an area #11.

                 GetFileArea 'ORDINAL' 10 'NAME'

                 Will return the name of area #11.

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETFILEFROMKEY
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetFileFromKey

   SYNOPSIS
       GetFileFromKey <KEY> [NEXT | NUMBER | NAME | SIZE | UPLOADED | LASTDL |
                      DLS | UPLOADER | < DESC [WRAP <NUM> MAXLINES <NUM>] >|
                      UNVALIDATED | OFFLINE | FREE]
   FUNCTION
       Traverse an area using a file key, or return information requested.

   INPUTS
       KEY         -- A file key obtained with "InitFileKey".
       NEXT        -- Move on to the next file. (remember <KEY> is still required)
       NAME        -- The name of the file.
       NUMBER      -- The number of the file.
       SIZE        -- Get the file's size.
       UPLOADED    -- Return the date the file was uploaded.
       LASTDL      -- The date the file was last downloaded.
       DLS         -- The number of times the file has been downloaded.
       UPLOADER    -- The name of the user who uploaded the file.
       UNVALIDATED -- Check if the file is unvalidated.
       FREE        -- Check if the file is free.
       OFFLINE     -- Check if the file is offline.
       WRAP        -- Wrap description after <NUM> chars.
       MAXLINES    -- Only return <NUM> lines of the description.
       DESC        -- Return the description.

   RESULT
       Requested information

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO
       @{"InitFileKey" link "InitFileKey"} @{"CloseFileKey" link "CloseFileKey"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETFULLPATH
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetFullPath

   SYNOPSIS
       GetFullPath '"<FILE>"'

   FUNCTION
       Find the physical path on disk of the given file (which
