@node GETPROTOCOLINFO
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetProtocolInfo

   SYNOPSIS
       GetProtocolInfo <AUTOUL | AUTODL | BATCH | LIBRARY | BIDIR |
                       LOWACCESS | HIACCESS | NAME | EXECUTABLE> <NUM>

   FUNCTION
       Get information on a given file transfer protocol. To get
       a list of protocols, loop around on this function increasing
       the number at each pass until RC = 10.

   INPUTS
       AUTOUL     -- Check if protocol accepts automatic uploads.   (BOOL)
       AUTODL     -- Check if protocol accepts automatic downloads. (BOOL)
       BATCH      -- Check if protocol accepts batch uploads.       (BOOL)
       LIBRARY    -- The name of the Executable or XPR library.
       BIDIR      -- Check if the protocol accepts BI-Directional Xfers. (BOOL)
       LOWACCESS  -- Minimum access required for this protocol.
       HIACCESS   -- Maximum access required for this protocol.
       NAME       -- The description of the protocol.
       EXECUTABLE -- Check if protocol is a library or an executable. (BOOL)
                     0 = Library, 1 = Executable programme.

       NUM        -- The number of the protocol to check.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Data retrieved and stored in RESULT.
       10 -- Could not get protocol info.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"ChangeXPRProto" link "ChangeXPRProto"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETSIG
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetSIG

   SYNOPSIS
       GetSIG <NUMBER <NUM>> <DIRECTORY | USETAG <NAME> | PARENT | TAG | DESC |
              LOW | HIGH | FAREAS | MAREAS | SUBDIRS | FITEMS | MITEMS>

   FUNCTION
       Get information on a specified special interest group.

   INPUTS
       NUMBER    -- The number of the SIG to get information on.

       DIRECTORY -- The directory path for the SIG.
       USETAG    -- Use the TAG NAME of the SIG instead of the NUMBER.
       PARENT    -- Parent of this SIG
       TAG       -- Tag (or name) of this SIG
       DESC      -- Description
       LOW       -- Lowest user access required to access SIG
       HIGH      -- Highest user access required to access SIG
       FAREAS    -- Number of file areas attached to SIG
       MAREAS    -- Number of message areas attached to SIG
       SUBDIRS   -- Number of sub-SIGs to this one
       FITEMS    -- Total number of files in all attached areas.
       MITEMS    -- Total number of messages in all attached areas.

   RESULT
       Information requested.

   RC
        0 -- Data retrieved and stored in RESULT.
        2 -- User does not have access to SIG.
        5 -- Bad SIG / No more SIGs in traversal
       10 -- Bad arguments.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"ChangeSIG" link "ChangeSIG"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETTEMPLATE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetTemplate

   SYNOPSIS
       GetTemplate [ORDINAL] <NUM> <DESCRIPTION|ACCESSLVL|CALLSDAY|MINSDAY|
                   FILERATIO|BYTERATIO|MAXBYTES|MAXFILES|FREEFILES|FREEBYTES|
                   MAXMSGS| FILERANGE <NUM> <LOW|HIGH|FLAGS> |
                   MSGRANGE <NUM> <LOW|HIGH|FLAGS> >


   FUNCTION
       Return information on a given Template.

   INPUTS
       ORDINAL -- See notes below
       NUM     -- Number of template to examine

       DESCRIPTION -- Description of template.
       ACCESSLVL   -- Access level this template is assigned to.
       CALLSDAY    --
       MINSDAY     --
       FILERATIO   --
       BYTERATIO   --
       MAXBYTES    --
       MAXFILES    --
       FREEFILES   --
       FREEBYTES   --
       MAXMSGS     --

       FILERANGE   -- Returns information on a given file area range in
                      this template.
         NUM       -- Number of file range to look at.
         LOW|HIGH|FLAGS -- Return either the low or high area range numbers
                           or the flags associated with them. See notes.

       MSGRANGE    -- Returns information on a given msg area range in
                      this template.
         NUM       -- Number of area range to look at.
         LOW|HIGH|FLAGS -- Return either the low or high area range numbers
                           or the flags associated with them. See notes.



   RESULT
       Information requested.

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        5 -- Template not found or end of template list
       10 -- Bad arguments.

       With FILERANGE and MSGRANGE functions:

        0 -- Successful
        5 -- Template not found or end of template list
        6 -- Message or File area range not found
       10 -- Bad arguments.


   EXAMPLE

       GetTemplate 'ORDINAL' 1 'DESCRIPTION'

       do until RC = 6
          GetTemplate 1 'FILERANGE' i 'LOW'
          Write '" Low  : 'RESULT'\n"'

          GetTemplate 1 'FILERANGE' i 'HIGH'
          Write '" High : 'RESULT'\n"'

          GetTemplate 1 'FILERANGE' i 'FLAGS'
          Write '" Flags: 'RESULT'\n"'
       end

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

       ORDINAL -- This keyword MUST appear before the NUM argument for it to
             work. The ORDINAL option is similiar to a NEXT keyword, meaning
             that if the specified number does not exist then the next available
             template will used.

             eg. If you do not have an area #10, but have an area #11.

                 GetTemplate 'ORDINAL' 10 'DESCRIPTION'

                 Will return the description of template #11.



       File and message area range flags are returned as a string of
       10 characters exactly as defined in the Templates program.


   SEE ALSO
       @{"SetTemplate" link "SetTemplate"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node GETTRANSFERFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       GetTransferFile

   SYNOPSIS
       GetTransferFile <SEND|RECV> <FIRST|LAST|NEXT|PREV>

   FUNCTION
       Obtains details of transfered files (details accessable
       via CC numbers).

   INPUTS
       SEND  -- Look at sent files only.
       RECV  -- Look at received files only.

       FIRST -- Obtain details on the first file transfered.
       LAST  -- Last file.
       NEXT  -- Next file in list.
       PREV  -- Previous file in list.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
       10 -- No more files / no file found

   EXAMPLE

        GetTransferFile 'SEND' 'FIRST'
        TRF = RC
        do while TRF = 0
                ExpandCC '"%1221|"'
                Bytes=RESULT
                Write '"%1220%-30s| 'Left(Bytes,8)' / %1222%-8ld| %1226%5ld|   %1224%3ld|%   %1223|\n"'

                GetTransferFile 'SEND' 'NEXT'
                TRF=RC
                end

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node INITFILEKEY
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       InitFileKey

   SYNOPSIS
       InitFileKey AREA <AREANUM> [ALPHA|CHRONO] [FWD|BWD]

   FUNCTION
       Obtains a lock on a file area for traversing the file list
       in a flexible way.  This function @{b}must@{ub} be followed
       by CloseFileKey once you have finished!

   INPUTS
       AREANUM -- Number of area to use.

       ALPHA   -- Read files in alphabetical order.
       CHRONO  -- Read files in order of age.
       NATURAL -- Read files in the order in which they
                  are in the file. DEFAULT.

       FWD     -- Read in forward order.
       BWD     -- Read in backward order.

   RESULT
       KEY     -- A file key which you @{b}must@{ub} keep for
                  use and deallocation later.

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        5 -- Error initialising scan.
       10 -- Bad args.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO
       @{"CloseFileKey" link "CloseFileKey"} @{"GetFileFromKey" link "GetFileFromKey"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node JUMPFILEAREA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       JumpFileArea

   SYNOPSIS
       JumpFileArea <NEXT|PREV|FIRST|LAST> [IGNORESIG] [IGNOREACCESS]

   FUNCTION
