@node MARKDOSFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MarkDOSFile

   SYNOPSIS
       MarkDOSFile <FILENAME> [CHECK]

   FUNCTION
       Adds a DOS file, not in Zeus' file catalogues, to the user's
       download list.  This is potentially dangerous if a user
       is allowed to specify files to download here themselves,
       as any file can specified including data and programs on
       your disks!

   INPUTS
       FILENAME -- File to mark for download.
       CHECK    -- Check if file is already marked, and also check
                   the user's file/byte ratio has enough left to
                   download the file. This makes MarkDOSFile act
                   more like a normal file marking.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        1 -- Failed, file is zero bytes
        2 -- File already marked
        3 -- File/byte ratio left is insufficient to download file.
        5 -- Failed to add marked file to user's marked file list.
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous | Line Number

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MARKFILES
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MarkFiles

   SYNOPSIS
       MarkFiles [FILE] [FILE] [ ... ]

   FUNCTION
       Mark one or more files for the online user to download.

   INPUTS
       FILE -- One or more files, either numbers or filenames.

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MASKFILEAREA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MaskFileArea

   SYNOPSIS
       MaskFileArea [AREA AreaNumber] [MASKIN] [MASKOUT] [TOGGLE] [SIG] [ALL]

   FUNCTION
       Mask file areas for the online user. If a file area is masked out,
       the user will not see the area during new file scans, etc.

   INPUTS
       AreaNumer -- Optional area number. If not given the current area is
                    used if necessary.

       MASKIN    -- Mask areas in.
       MASKOUT   -- Mask areas out.
       TOGGLE    -- Toggle areas - if the are masked in, they are masked out
                    and if they are masked out they are masked in.

       SIG       -- Perform mask on the whole of the current SIG instead of
                    the one area.
       ALL       -- Perform mask on ALL areas.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MOVEFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MoveFile

   SYNOPSIS
       MoveFile [FILENAME <Name>] [AREA <Area>]

   FUNCTION
       Moves a file from one area into another.

   INPUTS
       Name -- File name/number to move
       Area -- Area number to move to

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        1 -- Error saving new file record
        2 -- Could not find source file area
        3 -- Could not find destination file area
        4 -- Could not delete original file entry
        5 -- Could not find file
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE
       MoveFile 'FileName' '"'Filename'"' 'Area' '"'NewArea'"'

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node NEXTMARK
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       NextMark

   SYNOPSIS
       NextMark

   FUNCTION
       Sets the current file (access throught CC numbers %10xx|)
       to the next marked file.

       This should be called immediatly after marking files using
       the ARexx command @{"MarkFiles" link "MarkFiles"} in order to determine if
       each file name passed was marked or not, in order to
       inform the user.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       File name of marked file.

   RC
        0 -- END of Marked files list.
        1 -- File was successfully marked for download.
        2 -- File does not exist
        3 -- File was already marked
        4 -- Undefined - should not happen.
        5 -- File would exceed byte ratio
        6 -- File would exceed file ratio
        7 -- User does not have access to the area the file is stored in
        8 -- User may not download from area file is stored in
        9 -- Undefined - should not happen.
       10 -- Bad arguments
       11 -- Maximum file marks exceeded (see FileConfig->General)
       12 -- File is unvalidated
       13 -- File is offline
       15 -- File catalogue error

   EXAMPLE

MarkFiles Files
if RC = 0 then do
    fin = 0
    do until fin = 1
        NextMark
        Mk = RC
        Name = RESULT

        Select
            When Mk = 0 then fin = 1
            When Mk = 1 then do
                Write '"\rMarked File ['Name']."' 'NoMore'
                end
            When Mk = 2 then do
                if Name ~= 'RESULT' then
                    Write '"\rError Marking ['Name']. File does not exist!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end
            When Mk = 3 then do
                if Name ~= 'RESULT' then
                    Write '"\rFile ['Name'] already marked!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end
            When Mk = 4 then nop

            When Mk = 5 then do
                Write '"\rSorry! You have exceeded your Byte Ratio!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 6 then do
                Write '"\rSorry! You have exceeded your File Ratio!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 7 then do
                /* User may not access area! */
                Write '"\rError Marking ['Name']. File does not exist!\n"' 'NoMore'
                WriteLog '*' '"User doesn't have area access for 'Name'. Told them it doesn't exist!"'
                end
            When Mk = 8 then do
                Write '"\rYou do not have Download Access for ['Name'].\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 9 then nop

            When Mk = 10 then do
                Write '"\rBad Arguments!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 11 then do
                Write '"\rMaximum File marks exceeded!\n"' 'NoMore'
                fin = 1
                end

            When Mk = 12 then do
                Write '"\rFile has not yet been validated by SysOp!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 13 then do
                Write '"\rThis file is currently offline!\n"' 'NoMore'
                end

            When Mk = 15 then do
                Write '"\rFile Catalogue error!\n"' 'NoMore'
                WriteLog '*' '"File Catalogue error trying to mark file 'Name'!"'
                end
            Otherwise do
                Write '"\rFatal Error RC 'RC'!\n"' 'NoMore'
                WriteLog '*' '"Fatal Error RC 'Mk' trying to mark file 'Name'!"'
                fin = 1
                end
            end
        end
    end
else do
    Write '"\nFatal Error!\n\n"'
    WaitReturn
    if RC ~= 0 then exit
    end

Write '"\n"'

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node NEXTSCANFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       NextScanFile

   SYNOPSIS
       NextScanFile

   FUNCTION
       Reads in the next file in a file scan.  See @{"InitFileScan" link "InitFileScan"}.

