@node SAVEFILE
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SaveFile

   SYNOPSIS
       SaveFile '"<FileName>"' [AREA <Area>]

   FUNCTION
       Saves a file into the Zeus file catalogues.  This also
       moves the file into the specified file area's directory.

       The description for the file is taken from the file
       "T:FileDesc.n" where n is the number of the line the save
       is being performed on.

   INPUTS
       FILENAME -- File to save in catalogue.
       AREA     -- Optional area to save in. Defaults to the
                   current file area.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        1 -- Invalid upload area
        2 -- Invalid file description
        3 -- File already exists on the BBS
        4 -- Bad file name (contains illegal characters)
        5 -- Error saving file
        6 -- No uploads allowed to specified area
        7 -- Could not get upload path for area
        8 -- Could not move/copy file to destination directory
             (already exists?)
       15 -- File directory error

   EXAMPLE

       SaveFile '"Files:Temp/Newfile.lzx"' AREA 1

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node SETFILEAREA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SetFileArea

   SYNOPSIS
       SetFileArea [AREA <AreaNum>] [NAME '"<Name>"'] [CLEARPATHS] [PATH '"<Path>"']
                   [PATHLIST '"<Path>"'] [LOW <LowAccess>] [HIGH <HighAccess>]
                   [DLBAUD <MinDlBaud>] [ULBAUD <MinUlBaud>] [AGE <MinAge>]
                   [SETRANDOM] [DOWNLOADS] [NODOWNLOADS] [UPLOADS]
                   [NOUPLOADS] [VIEWING] [NOVIEWING] [FREEFILES]
                   [NOFREEFILES] [DOSNAMES] [NODOSNAMES] [VALIDATION]
                   [NOVALIDATION] [COPYTOTEMP] [NOCOPYTOTEMP] [FILELIB '"<Name>"']
                   [SAVE] [REMOVEALL] [RELOAD]

   FUNCTION
       Set an existing file area's settings or create a new area.

       This function also controls the loading and saving of the
       file area configuration.

       This can be used to create a new file configuration by
       first using "SetFileArea REMOVEALL", setting your areas,
       then using "SetFileArea SAVE" which overwrites the
       previous settings with your new ones.

   INPUTS
       AREA     -- Number of area to work on. If the area number does
                   not exist, it is created.
       NAME     -- Change name of area.
       CLEARPATHS -- Remove all MultiPaths.
       PATH     -- Set main path of area.
       PATHLIST -- Add one path to the MultiPath list.
       LOW      -- Set low access limit.
       HIGH     -- Set high access limit.
       DLBAUD   -- Set minimum download speed.
       ULBAUD   -- Set minimum upload speed.
       AGE      -- Set minimum age a user has to be to access this area.
       SETRANDOM -- Obsolete function. Sets the area's "unique" field.

       DOWNLOADS    -- Allow downloads.
       NODOWNLOADS  -- Do not allow downloads.
       UPLOADS      -- Allow uploads.
       NOUPLOADS    -- Do not allow uploads.
       VIEWING      -- Allow viewing files.
       NOVIEWING    -- Do not allow viewing files.
       FREEFILES    -- Area contains free downloads.
       NOFREEFILES  -- Do not allow free downloads unless specific file
                       is free a download
       DOSNAMES     -- Use MS-DOS 8.3 file name style.
       NODOSNAMES   -- Use Amiga file names.
       VALIDATION   -- Files require validation after upload.
       NOVALIDATION -- Files do not require validation after upload.
       COPYTOTEMP   -- Copy files to Temp directory before download.
       NOCOPYTOTEMP -- Do now copy files to Temp directory before download.
       FILELIB      -- Change File Base library. MUST specify the library's
                       @{b}file name@{ub}.

       SAVE      -- Save areas.
       REMOVEALL -- Remove all areas from memory.
       RELOAD    -- Reload file area configuration.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        5 -- File area not found / could not be created
       10 -- Bad arguments / file library not found

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node SETFILEFILTER
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SetFileFilter

   SYNOPSIS
       SetFileFilter [DATE '"<date>"'] [SINCE] [BEFORE]
                     [FILENAME '"<filename>"'] [DESC '"<desc>"']
                     [TEXT '"<text>"']

   FUNCTION
       Sets a filter for future file operations which causes only
       files matching the filter to be displayed.

   INPUTS
       DATE     -- Date to process files on in the format
                   "dd-mmm-yy". e.g. "30-Jun-99"

       SINCE    -- Match files uploaded since specified date.
       BEFORE   -- Match files uploaded before specified date.
       FILENAME -- Match filename.
       DESC     -- Match description.
       TEXT     -- Match both filename and description.

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        5 -- Incorrect date string.
       10 -- Bad arguments.


   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"NextFileScan" link "NextFileScan"} @{"CheckNewFiles" link "CheckNewFiles"} @{"DeleteFileFilter" link "DeleteFileFilter"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node SETTEMPLATES
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SetTemplates

   SYNOPSIS
       SetTemplates [CLEAR] [RELOAD] [SAVE] [ACCESS 'Level']
                    [DESCRIPTION '"Desc"'] [CALLSDAY 'Calls'] [MINSCALL 'Mins']
                    [MINSDAY 'Mins'] [FILERATIO 'Ratio'] [BYTERATIO 'Ratio']
                    [MAXBYTES 'Bytes'] [MAXFILES 'Files'] [FREEFILES 'Num']
                    [FREEBYTES 'Num'] [MAXMSGS 'Msgs']
                    [ADDFILERANGE 'Low' 'High' '"Flags"']
                    [ADDMSGRANGE 'Low' 'High' '"Flags"'] [CLEARMSGRANGES]
                    [CLEARFILERANGES]


   FUNCTION
       Alters the Template settings.

       This function also controls the loading and saving of the
       template area configuration.

       This can be used to create a new configuration by first using
       "CLEAR", setting your templates, then using "SAVE" which
       overwrites the previous settings with your new ones.

   INPUTS
       CLEAR           -- Clear current template configuration
       RELOAD          -- Reload existing configuration on disk
       SAVE            -- Save new template configuration

       ACCESS          -- Template access level to change.
                          If this access level exists, the given settings
                          will alter the existing template. If it does not
                          exist, a new template will be created.
       DESCRIPTION     -- Set the template description

       CALLSDAY        -- Maximum calls per day users with this template
                          can make.
       MINSCALL        -- Maximum minutes per call
       MINSDAY         -- Maximum minutes per day
       FILERATIO       -- File ratio
       BYTERATIO       -- Byte ratio
       MAXBYTES        -- Maximum bytes that may be downloaded per day
       MAXFILES        -- Maximum files that may be downloaded per day
       FREEFILES       -- Number of files that may be downloaded before
                          the ratio comes into effect
       FREEBYTES       -- Total bytes that may be downloaded before
                          the ratio comes into effect
       MAXMSGS         -- Maximum number of messages that may be written
                          per day.

       ADDFILERANGE    -- Add a new file range:
          LOW           - Bottom of range
          HIGH          - Top of range
          FLAGS         - Flags for range. See notes

       ADDMSGRANGE     -- Add a new message range:
          LOW           - Bottom of range
          HIGH          - Top of range
          FLAGS         - Flags for range. See notes

       CLEARMSGRANGES  -- Clear all message ranges
       CLEARFILERANGES -- Clear all file ranges

   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        5 -- Error loading/saving templates
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
       Asynchronous

       File and message area range flags are returned as a string of
       10 characters exactly as defined in the Templates program.

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node SETUSERFILEDATA
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SetUserFileData

   SYNOPSIS
       SetUserFileData <FILESDL|BYTESDL|FILESUL|BYTESUL|FILERATIO|BYTERATIO|
                        FREEFILES|FREEBYTES|MAXFILES|MAXBYTES|BYTESTODAY|
                        FILESTODAY|PROTOCOL|FILEAREA|LASTSCANDATE|SIG> 'Data'
                       [USER 'Key']

   FUNCTION
       Changes various statistics and other information about either the
       current or given user.


       *@{b}WARNING@{ub}*: This function appears to be malfunctioning.  It
       appears to clear the user's current file area and file protocol.

       It is recommended that this function is not used until this problem
       has been fully investigated.


   INPUTS
       USER         -- User key to act on, as given by UserFromKey. If not
                       given, the currently online user is acted on.

       FILESDL      -- Set total number of files the user has downloaded
       BYTESDL      -- Set total bytes the user has downloaded
       FILESUL      -- Set total number of files the user has uploaded
       BYTESUL      -- Set total bytes the user has uploaded
       FILERATIO    -- Set user's file ratio
       BYTERATIO    -- Set user's byte ratio
       MAXBYTES     -- Maximum bytes that may be downloaded per day
       MAXFILES     -- Maximum files that may be downloaded per day
       FREEFILES    -- Number of files that may be downloaded before
                       the ratio comes into effect
       FREEBYTES    -- Total bytes that may be downloaded before
                       the ratio comes into effect
       BYTESTODAY   -- Total of bytes downloaded today
       FILESTODAY   -- Total of files downloaded today
       LASTSCANDATE -- Last time the user scanned for new files
       PROTOCOL     -- File transfer protocol
       FILEAREA     -- Current file area
       SIG          -- Current SIG

   RESULT

   RC
       0 -- Successful

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous 

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node SIMPLELIST
@toc File
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       SimpleList

   SYNOPSIS
       SimpleList [ALL] [SIG] [AREA <Area>] [ALPHA|CHRONO] [FORWARDS|BACKWARDS]
                  [NEW '"Date"'] [OLD '"Date"'] [TEXT '"String"']
                  [DESC '"String"'] [FILENAME '"String"'] [UNVALIDATED]
                  [MAXLINES <Num>]

   FUNCTION
       Initalise a SimpleList for displaying files interactively to
       the online user.

   INPUTS
       ALL      -- Scan all file areas.
       SIG      -- Scan all areas in the current SIG.
       AREA     -- Specify a single area to scan.

       ALPHA    -- Scan files in alphabetical order.
       CHRONO   -- Scan files in order of age.

       FORWARDS -- Ascending order.
       BACKWARDS -- Decending order.

       NEW      -- Show files uploaded during or after the given date.
       OLD      -- Show files uploaded during or before the given date.

       TEXT     -- Files where the description and file name contain
                   the given string.
       DESC     -- Files where the description contains the given string.
       FILENAME -- Files where the name contains the given string.

       UNVALIDATED -- Scan for unvalidated files.

       MAXLINES -- Maximum number of description lines to display.


   RESULT

   RC
        0 -- Successful
        3 -- Missing needed Language strings
       10 -- Bad arguments

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"EndList" link "EndList"} @{"PageList" link "PageList"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

