   RESULT

   RC

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node "Mailer.CALL"
@toc Mailer
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Call

   SYNOPSIS
       Call <Number|FidoNet Address> [NOEMSI]

   FUNCTION
       Calls the number or address specified.  ZMailer will attempt to
       call the given number, if busy, the number of times specified
       in ZMailer preferences.

       Some older FidoNet mailers which do no support the EMSI mailer
       standard do not correctly refuse it; such as MAX's BBS.  To call
       a system which behaves like this, specify the NoEMSI argument.
       ZMailer will drop, for this call, to the FTS-1 (LoTek) protocol
       for negotiation.  The disadvantage of doing this is that the
       FTS-1 protocol presents only one address.

   INPUTS
       <Number|FidoNet Address>     -- number to call.
       [NOEMSI]                     -- Disable EMSI for this call.

   RESULT
        0 -- Successful
       10 -- Unknown number/address

   RC

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

