@node pnxrexx.PnxGetCompressStr
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxGetCompressStr

   SYNOPSIS
      PnxGetCompressStr <ArcNo>

   FUNCTION
      Returns the compress string of archiver <ArcNo>. In the string
      there should be a ~a. You should place the name of the archive
      to make here. There should also be a ~f. You should replace this
      with the file(s) to compress.

   NOTES

   INPUTS
      ArcNo    A number of an archiver in Zeus' configuration.

   RESULT
      RC  0 Ok, the compress string should be in RESULT.
      RC  5 Bad arguments.
      RC 11 Couldn't find archiver.

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node pnxrexx.PnxGetConfig                                     pnxrexx.PnxGetConfig
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxGetConfig

   SYNOPSIS
      PnxGetConfig <CHARSET|ARCHIVER|PKTTYPE|MAXAREA|MAXPKT|NEWS|HELLO|
                    GOODBYE|FILELIST|INDEX|FROMUSER|ALLNEW|BULLETINS|
                    WRAP|LASTPKTDL|NOSCHEDULER|ASYNCGRAB|TWIT> [user name]

   FUNCTION
      Returns information from user's Phoenix setings.

   NOTES
      If you launch it as an async command you must supply the name of the
      user. The name must be the last (second) argument.

   INPUTS
      CharSet     Obsolete
      Archiver    User's archiver
      PktType     User's packet format (QWK, MBBS etc)
      MaxArea     User's max msgs/area
      MaxPkt      User's max msgs/packet
      News        Include news file
      Hello       Include hello file
      Goodbye     Include goodbye file
      Filelist    Include file list
      Index       Create QWK .NDX files
      FromUser    Include msgs from the user
      AllNew      Messages will be dumped from high pointer, not last x.
      Bulletins   Include new bulletins since last logon
      Wrap        Where to wrap messages
      LastPktDl   When the user last downloaded a mail packet (N/A now)
      NoScheduler User shouldn't have access to the scheduler system
      AsyncGrab   Packet should be generated in the background

      UserName    Name of user if command is used as an async command.

   RESULT
      RC 0  Ok, requested info is in RESULT
      RC 5  Bad arguments
      RC 10 Couldn't get line
      RC 11 Couldn't load user
      RC 12 Couldn't load user's XData
      RC 13 Couldn't get user's Phoenix config (Use PnxSetConfig to
            create one)

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
      PnxSetConfig PnxRemConfig

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node pnxrexx.PnxGetErrorMsg                                 pnxrexx.PnxGetErrorMsg
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxGetErrorMsg

   SYNOPSIS
