@node pnxrexx.PnxSetConfig                                     pnxrexx.PnxSetConfig
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxSetConfig

   SYNOPSIS
      PnxSetConfig [USER <user name>] [CHARSET <data>] [ARCHIVER <data>]
                   [PKTTYPE <data>] [MAXAREA <data>] [MAXPKT <data>]
                   [NEWS <data>] [HELLO <data>] [GOODBYE <data>]
                   [FILELIST <data>] [INDEX <data>] [FROMUSER <data>]
                   [ALLNEW <data>] [BULLETINS <data>] [WRAP <data>]
                   [LASTPKTDL] [NOSCHEDULER <data>] [ASYNCGRAB <data>]
                   [TWIT <data>]

   FUNCTION
      Will set some data in the user's Phoenix configuration. If the
      user didn't have a configuration it will have now.

   NOTES
      This function scans all your arguments and parses them. I.e. you
      can set several fields in just one call.

      If used as an async command you *must* supply the 'USER' keyword
      and user name before any other arguments.

   INPUTS
      UserName    Name of user if command is used as an async command.
                  MUST be the first argument.

      CharSet     Obsolete
      Archiver    User's archiver
      PktType     User's packet format (0 QWK, 1 Bluewave, 2 MBBS)
      MaxArea     User's max msgs/area
      MaxPkt      User's max msgs/packet
      News        Include news file
      Hello       Include hello file
      Goodbye     Include goodbye file
      Filelist    Include file list
      Index       Create QWK .NDX files
      FromUser    Include msgs from the user
      AllNew      Messages will be dumped from high pointer, not last x.
      Bulletins   Include new bulletins since last logon
      Wrap        Where to wrap messages
      LastPktDl   Sets when the user last downloaded a mail packet to
                  current time.
      NoScheduler User shouldn't have access to the scheduler system
      AsyncGrab   Packet should be generated in the background

   RESULT
      RC  0 Ok
      RC  5 Bad arguments
      RC 10 Couldn't get line
      RC 11 Couldn't load user
      RC 12 Couldn't load user's XData
      RC 13 Couldn't set twit filter
      RC 14 Couldn't add new configuration
      RC 15 Couldn't save configuration

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO
      PnxGetConfig PnxRemConfig

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node pnxrexx.PnxSetSchedule                                 pnxrexx.PnxSetSchedule
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxSetSchedule

   SYNOPSIS
      PnxSetSchedule <[ADD <day> <hour> <min>] | [DROP <day>]> <user name>

   FUNCTION
      Adds or drops a weekday the scheduler should automatically make
      a mail packet for ä user.

   NOTES

   INPUTS
      ADD      Add a weekday.
      DROP     Drop a weekday.
      day      A weekday (Monday = 0, Tuesday = 1 etc)
      hour     Hours after midnight.
      min      Minutes after the hour.
      UserName Name of user.

   RESULT
      RC  0 Ok
      RC  5 Bad arguments
      RC 11 Couldn't load user
      RC 12 Couldn't get user's Phoenix config
      RC 13 User isn't allowed to use the scheduler system.
      RC 14 Out of memory

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node pnxrexx.PnxStopExport                                   pnxrexx.PnxStopExport
@toc Phoenix
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
      PnxStopExport

   SYNOPSIS
      PnxStopExport <user name> [CANCEL]

   FUNCTION
      Aborts or stops an async grab. If the CANCEL argument isn't given
      the mail packet will be generated, however no more messages will be
      dumped.

   NOTES

   INPUTS
      UserName    Name of user, which mail packet should be stoped.
      CANCEL      Completly abort the package.

   RESULT
      RC  0 Exporter found, and aborted.
      RC  5 Bad arguments.
      RC 11 Exporter not found.

   BUGS

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

