@node UEDDisplayUser
@toc UED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       UEDDisplayUser

   SYNOPSIS
       UEDDisplayUser '"<TEXT>"'

   FUNCTION
       Displays some text to user in a requester, pausing the ARexx
       script until a response is given.

   INPUTS
       TEXT  --  message to place in the requester.

   RC

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node UEDRequest
@toc UED
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       UEDRequest

   SYNOPSIS
       UEDRequest <Text> [Buttons] [Title]

   FUNCTION
       Opens a window, as with UEDDisplayUser, but also allows
       the user to specify between given options.

   INPUTS
       Text    -- Text to display to the user.
       Buttons -- The buttons of the requester. Each button is
                  separated by a "|". Defaults to "Yes|No".
       Title   -- If buttons are given, then a title may be
                  specified also. Defaults to "Important
                  Request".

   RESULT

   RC
       10 -- Bad arguments.

       Otherwise, the number of the button the user specified,
       0 representing the far right option (most negative)
       then starting with 1 on the left. i.e.:

            "Yes|Maybe|No"

              1    2    0

   EXAMPLE

       /**/

       options results

       address ZEUS
       UEDRequest '"Hello from the test script"' '"Hi|Hello|Goodbye"' '"Hihi"'
       say RC

   NOTES
       Note that you cannot safely have 11 buttons as 10 is
       used as an error return code.

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

