@endnode

@node INITUSERKEY
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       InitUserKey -- Initialise a userkey for traversing the user list.

   SYNOPSIS
       InitUserKey <ALPHAFORWARD|ALPHAREVERSE|CHRONOFORWARD|CHRONOREVERSE>

   FUNCTION
       Initialises a user key for traversing the user list in the given
       direction.
       
   INPUTS
       ALPHAFORWARD  - Go forward alphabetically
       ALPHAREVERSE  - Go backwards alphabetically
       CHRONOFORWARD - Go forwards chronologically
       CHRONOREVERSE - Go backwards chronologically

    RC
       0 - Userkey initialised.
      10 - Bad arguments or out of memory.

    RESULT
        Contains a pointer to a UserKey for use with the other userkey
        functions.

    NOTES
        The first user record is already loaded into the key after
        calling this function.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous  

   SEE ALSO
       @{"UserFromKey" link "UserFromKey"} @{"GetKeyAlias" link "GetKeyAlias"} @{"NextUserKey" link "NextUserKey"} @{"EndUserKey" link "EndUserKey"} @{"GetKeyName" link "GetKeyName"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node ISUSERONLINE
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       IsUserOnline -- Check if a user is currently online.

   SYNOPSIS
       IsUserOnline '"'<User Name>'"'

   FUNCTION
       Checks all the lines to see if the given user is online.  If the
       user is online, the line number that the user is connected to is
       returned.
       
   INPUTS
       UserName - May be a users name or their alias.

    RC
       0 - User is online.
       5 - User is not online.
      10 - User name not given.

    RESULT
       If RC == 0 then RESULT will contain the line number that the user is
       connected to.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous  

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node KILLSCRIPT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       KillScript -- Tells Zeus that no more scripts are to be run on
                     this line.

   SYNOPSIS
       KillScript

   FUNCTION
       This function will stop all scripts being run on the current line.
       It will not be needed for most purposes but is there for anyone who
       needs it.  It can be countered by a call to StartUp.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node LASTINPUT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       LastInput

   SYNOPSIS
       LastInput

   FUNCTION
       Retrieves the last thing the user typed.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       What the user last typed.

   RC
       0 -- Successful. Last input retrieved and stored in RESULT.
