@node LASTSCRIPT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       LastScript -- Tells Zeus the last script is the next script.

   SYNOPSIS
       LastScript

   FUNCTION
       Sets the next script to the previous script.  When the current
       script exits, Zeus will run the script the current script was
       called from.  This can be used in scripts which are subroutines of
       other scripts.

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node LOADUSER
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       LoadUser -- Loads a user from disk.

   SYNOPSIS
       LoadUser '"<Name>"'

   FUNCTION
       LoadUser will first scan the internal user list in memory and if the
       user cannot be found there, it will attempt to load the user off the
       disk.

   INPUTS
       Name - The name of the user to load.

   RC
        0 - User could not be loaded.
       >0 - A pointer to a user structure.  This can be passed to PutOnline
           later on.

   NOTES
       Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node LOADUSERXDATA
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       LoadUserXData -- Loads a users extra database into memory.

   SYNOPSIS
       LoadUserXData <User>

   FUNCTION
       To access a users extra database it must be loaded into memory.  This
       is automatically done for a user who is PUTONLINE but if you wish to
       access other users db you use this function.

   INPUTS
       User - User pointer as obtained by LoadUser.

   RC
        0 - DB loaded.
       10 - Bad args.
       20 - Illegal user pointer/no user online.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
       Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MAILERQUIT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MailerQuit -- Tells the mailer that the call has ended.

   SYNOPSIS
       MailerQuit

   FUNCTION
       When a mailer runs MailerStart it becomes locked until you call this
       function.  Calling this function magically awakens the mailer and it
       will reset ready for the next call.  You should then call MailerWait
       again.

   SEE ALSO
       @{"MailerWait" link MailerWait}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MAILERWAIT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MailerWait -- Waits for the signal generated by 'MailerStart', etc.

   SYNOPSIS
       MailerWait

   FUNCTION
       If you are running a front end mailer, you can have your
       script wait until the a call has been answered by using
       this command. Your mailer should call the MailerStart
       program which will in turn 'wake up' your script.

       ZMailer or other Zeus provided front end program will call
       an internal equivilent of MailerStart themselves, which in
       turn also signals this MailerWait command.

   SEE ALSO
       @{"MailerQuit" link MailerQuit}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node MAKENEWUSER
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       MakeNewUser -- Makes a new user structure.

   SYNOPSIS
       MakeNewUser '"<Name>"'

   FUNCTION
       MakeNewUser allocates and initialises a user structure for a new
       user.

   INPUTS
       Name - The name of the user which will be filled into the struct.

   RC
        0 - User was created.
       10 - Out of memory or bad arguments.

   RESULT
       Contains the pointer to the new user for use with PutOnline.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
          Asynchronous  

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node NEXTSCRIPT
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       NextScript -- Sets the name of the next script to execute.

   SYNOPSIS
       NextScript "<ScriptName>"

   FUNCTION
       Sets the name of the next script to execute when the current script
       exits.

   INPUTS
       ScriptName - Name of the next script to run.  If the script is in
                    the 'Zeus:Scripts/' directory then no path is
                    needed.  If the script ends in '.zeus' then no extension
                    needs to be given.

   RC
       0 - NextScript was set.
      10 - Bad Arguments.

   NOTES
       Doesn't actually check to see if the script exists.  If it doesn't,
       or if there is an error in the next script, Zeus will jump back
       to the previous script.

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

