   SEE ALSO
       @{"LoadUser" link "LoadUser"} @{"MakeNewUser" link "MakeNewUser"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node QUITZEUS
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       QuitZeus -- Shuts down the entire Zeus system.

   SYNOPSIS
       QuitZeus

   FUNCTION
       Closes down Zeus entirely, freeing all memory and
       terminating all programs.

   INPUTS

   RESULT
       Results in withdrawal symptoms developing within 24 hours
       for a normal sysop.

   RC
       0 -- Always Successful.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES
       Asynchronous

   SEE ALSO

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

@node READ
@toc AlphaIndex
@rem <PRE>

   NAME
       Read -- Get data from the user online.

   SYNOPSIS
       Read [ADDHIST '"<STR>"'] [ANIM '"<STR>"'] [DEFSTR '"<STR>"'] [HOT] [ISMENU]
            [MAKELOWER] [MAKENICE] [MAKEUPPER] [MAXLEN <NUM>] [MINLEN <NUM>]
            [NONEWLINE] [NOSHOW] [NOWAIT] [ONLYALPHA] [ONLYCHARS] [ONLYNUMS]
            [OPTS '<STR>'] [RESET] [SECRET] [SHOWMSGS] [STRIP] [TIMEOUT <NUM>]
            [USEHIST] [XOPT '<STR>']

   FUNCTION
       General purpose way to get data from the user.

   INPUTS
       ADDHIST   -- A string to add to the history buffer.
       ANIM      -- A string to animate for the prompt if the user has animated
                    ANSI enabled. For this to work, you must also specify HOT
                    and NOSHOW - animation doesn't make sense otherwise.
                    Set the speed using "\sSPEED" anywhere in the string, any
                    number of times.  E.g. "\s10"

       DEFSTR    -- A default string to place into the input stream. The user may
                    change it if desired.

       HOT       -- Tells "Read" to only read 1 character immediately. Equivilant
                    to having hotkeys turned on but this is forced.

       ISMENU    -- Tells "Read" to follow user settings, ie. if the user has
                    hotkeys or not.

       MAKELOWER -- Make the result of the input all lower case text.
       MAKENICE  -- Format the result of the input to proper name capitilization.
       MAKEUPPER -- Make the result of the string all upper case.
       MAXLEN    -- Maximum number of characters to read from the input.
       MINLEN    -- Minimum number of characters to read from the input.
       NONEWLINE -- Do not send a line feed when the user hits return.
       NOSHOW    -- Do not echo output to the user while typing.
       NOWAIT    -- Return right away if no input is waiting in the stream. Use
                    this in conjunctioin with the HOT option.
       ONLYALPHA -- No Hi-ASCII 8bit input will be permitted.
       ONLYCHARS -- Only allow letters A to Z and spaces.
       ONLYNUMS  -- Only Numbers may be entered.
       OPTS      -- Only these specified characters can be entered.
       RESET     -- Send an ANSI reset code when the user presses return.
       SECRET    -- Echo a '*' when the user types. Useful for passwords.
       SHOWMSGS  -- Recieve multi-line messages while a user is at a prompt.
       STRIP     -- Strip the leading and trailing spaces from the result.
       TIMEOUT   -- The number of microseconds to wait before input times out.
       USEHIST   -- Use the history buffer.
       XOPT      -- User may not enter any of these characters.

   RESULT
       The data the user entered.

   RC
        0 -- User input retrieved and stored in RESULT.
        5 -- User dropped carrier or carrier lost.
       20 -- Line is shutting down.

   EXAMPLE

   NOTES

   SEE ALSO
       @{"Prompt" link "Prompt"} @{"ClearHistory" link "ClearHistory"} @{"Write" link "Write"}

@rem </PRE>
@endnode

